				<div class="TU"><br><ul><li>These results indicate that the single and double glycine substitutions did not affect the ability of ArsR to repress its own synthesis , but did prevent these proteins from responding to inducer .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8621591" target="_blank">8621591</a>]<br></li>
<li>It encodes an arsenic-inducibletrans-acting repressor ( ArsR ) , controlling the basal level of expression of the operon ( San Francisco et al. 1990 ; Wu and Rosen 1991 , 1993 ~ ) a ; negative regulator ( ArsD ) that independently controls the upper level of expression of the operon ( Wu and Rosen 1993b ) ; an arsenite - and antimonite-stimulatedATPase ( ArsA ) ( Rosen et al. 1988 ; Mei-Hsu et al. 1991 ) ; a membrane pump for efflux of arsenite and antimonite ions ( ArsB ) ( Wu et al. 1992 ; Dey and Rosen 1995 ) ; and an arsenate reductase ( ArsC ) ( Rosen et al. 1991 ; Gladysheva et al. 1994 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8764681" target="_blank">8764681</a>]<br></li>
<li>Inductionof arsR genes was detected by immunoblot analysis of the ArsR proteins ( Fig. 3 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8051064" target="_blank">8051064</a>]<br></li>
<li>It is clear that expression of chimeric proteins in which [ i-lactamase was fused to the C-terminal region of ArsR ( pBLR102 and pBLR105 ) were inducibie both by arsenite ( Fig. 3 ) and arsenate ( data not shown ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1838573" target="_blank">1838573</a>]<br></li>
<li>Whileexpression of the arsB gene is inducedby sublethaldoses of arsenite in the presence of a functional arsR gene product , the role of the arsR gene product can be deducedfrom its strong homology with the ArsR protein encoded by the R773 ars operon , and examined using the arsR : : luxAB fusion strains .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8764681" target="_blank">8764681</a>]<br></li>
<li>Tc determine the function of the ArsR protein , a genetic analysis of its role in regulation of ars expression was undertaken using fusions of the btaM gene to the arsR gene .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1838573" target="_blank">1838573</a>]<br></li>
<li>By construction and expression of a series of in-frame fusions between truncated arsR genes and the coding region for the mature form of b-lactamase ( blaM * ) , it was shown that ArsR is a trans-acting repressor that regulates expression of the chromosomal ars operon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8576202" target="_blank">8576202</a>]<br></li>
<li>The arsR gene product , the ArsR repressor , was expressed and purified .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8576202" target="_blank">8576202</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression and Purification of ArsR Protein -- The arsR gene was isolated from the E. coli chromosomal ars operon by PCR , and ArsR was substantially purified .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8576202" target="_blank">8576202</a>]<br></li>
<li>plasmid-borne ars operons , transcription was controlled by the ArsR repressor , the product of the first gene of each operon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8576202" target="_blank">8576202</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription of the ars operon is regulated by a substrate-responsive repressor , the ArsR protein .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8621591" target="_blank">8621591</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , it is likely that the chromosomal ars operon is organized as a single transcription unit that is regulated by the arsenic - and antimony-inducible ArsR repressor .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7721697" target="_blank">7721697</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression of the gene for His6-tagged ArsR repressed lacZ expression in the absence of inducer and induced in the presence of sodium arsenite .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9188467" target="_blank">9188467</a>]<br></li>
<li>It can be concluded , therefore , that arsfl expression is autoregulated : expression is repressed by ArsR in the absence of arsenical inducers and is induced in their presence .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1838573" target="_blank">1838573</a>]<br></li>
<li>When the culture reached an A600 of 0.8 , expression of the arsR gene was induced by addition of 0.5 mM isopropyl-1-thio-b-D-galactopyranoside for an additional 3 h. Under these growth conditions , the majority of ArsR was found as a soluble protein in the cytosolic fraction .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8576202" target="_blank">8576202</a>]<br></li>
<li>The resuits demonstrate that the ArsR protein is a frans-acting regulatory protein which controls its own expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1838573" target="_blank">1838573</a>]<br></li>
